in purchasing power.

00:37:04.510 --> 00:37:05.210 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Unbelievable.

00:37:05.210 --> 00:37:06.010 align:middle line:90%
>>GRIFFIN: Yeah.

00:37:06.010 --> 00:37:09.760 align:middle line:90%
And that's since 1913.

00:37:09.760 --> 00:37:13.380 align:middle line:84%
That's almost
within the lifetime

00:37:13.380 --> 00:37:15.400 align:middle line:84%
of-- probably a few
people alive this still

00:37:15.400 --> 00:37:17.860 align:middle line:90%
saw the whole thing happen.

00:37:17.860 --> 00:37:20.570 align:middle line:84%
But it's generational and
it's going on all the time.

00:37:20.570 --> 00:37:22.570 align:middle line:84%
And it's part of the plan,
it's not an accident.

00:37:22.570 --> 00:37:23.457 align:middle line:90%
The people that--

00:37:23.457 --> 00:37:25.790 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, like you said,
they're not stupid people.

00:37:25.790 --> 00:37:27.331 align:middle line:84%
>>GRIFFIN: They're
not stupid people.

00:37:27.331 --> 00:37:31.180 align:middle line:84%
And they know that as long
as they can be whittled away

00:37:31.180 --> 00:37:34.720 align:middle line:84%
at purchasing power 3%
to 5% or 6% per year,

00:37:34.720 --> 00:37:36.700 align:middle line:84%
people will grumble but
they'll put up with it.

00:37:36.700 --> 00:37:37.950 align:middle line:90%
And they get old and they die.

00:37:37.950 --> 00:37:39.450 align:middle line:84%
Their kids don't
know any different,

00:37:39.450 --> 00:37:42.270 align:middle line:84%
they don't know
what $1 used to buy.

00:37:42.270 --> 00:37:43.395 align:middle line:90%
And so they put up with it.

00:37:43.395 --> 00:37:46.530 align:middle line:84%
It's this gradual transition,
one generation to the other.

00:37:46.530 --> 00:37:49.380 align:middle line:84%
And it's a way of
milking society

00:37:49.380 --> 00:37:56.390 align:middle line:84%
of their purchasing power
by the economic scientists.

00:37:56.390 --> 00:37:59.560 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How does the Federal
Reserve interact, if they do,

00:37:59.560 --> 00:38:00.555 align:middle line:90%
with world banks?

00:38:00.555 --> 00:38:03.144 align:middle line:90%


00:38:03.144 --> 00:38:05.185 align:middle line:84%
>>GRIFFIN: How do they
interact with world banks?

00:38:05.185 --> 00:38:07.170 align:middle line:84%
Well, world banks and
the Federal Reserve

00:38:07.170 --> 00:38:11.390 align:middle line:90%
are sort of joined at the hip.

00:38:11.390 --> 00:38:14.870 align:middle line:90%
They're like Siamese twins.

00:38:14.870 --> 00:38:17.790 align:middle line:84%
The World Bank is--
you might consider it

00:38:17.790 --> 00:38:21.085 align:middle line:84%
as the central
bank of the world.

00:38:21.085 --> 00:38:22.960 align:middle line:84%
The Federal Reserve
Board is the central bank

00:38:22.960 --> 00:38:23.835 align:middle line:90%
of the United States.

00:38:23.835 --> 00:38:25.049 align:middle line:90%
They're both central banks.

00:38:25.049 --> 00:38:26.840 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But they
interact with each other?

00:38:26.840 --> 00:38:28.548 align:middle line:84%
>>GRIFFIN: They interact
with each other.

00:38:28.548 --> 00:38:30.654 align:middle line:84%
They share assets, they
support each other.

00:38:30.654 --> 00:38:32.320 align:middle line:84%
People go to work
from one to the other,

00:38:32.320 --> 00:38:33.690 align:middle line:90%
they move from one to the other.

00:38:33.690 --> 00:38:39.660 align:middle line:84%
The philosophy is the same,
except that the objective,

00:38:39.660 --> 00:38:42.480 align:middle line:84%
of course, is
international with the IMF,

00:38:42.480 --> 00:38:45.660 align:middle line:84%
whereas with the Federal
Reserve System it's national,

00:38:45.660 --> 00:38:46.500 align:middle line:90%
theoretically.

00:38:46.500 --> 00:38:49.340 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I have heard,
this is what I heard,

00:38:49.340 --> 00:38:53.980 align:middle line:84%
that they like to loan
money to Third World nations

00:38:53.980 --> 00:38:57.320 align:middle line:84%
and force them to default
so they can take over

00:38:57.320 --> 00:39:01.050 align:middle line:84%
their assets, be it the
land or the country itself.

00:39:01.050 --> 00:39:02.640 align:middle line:90%
Did you ever hear of that?

00:39:02.640 --> 00:39:03.790 align:middle line:90%
>>GRIFFIN: Oh, yes.

00:39:03.790 --> 00:39:06.210 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: They don't want
the loans paid back.

00:39:06.210 --> 00:39:08.460 align:middle line:90%
>>GRIFFIN: Well, that's true.

00:39:08.460 --> 00:39:10.320 align:middle line:84%
Why would they want
a loan paid back when

00:39:10.320 --> 00:39:12.160 align:middle line:90%
they could get the country?

00:39:12.160 --> 00:39:13.610 align:middle line:90%
That's what they really want.

00:39:13.610 --> 00:39:13.870 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's the goal?

00:39:13.870 --> 00:39:14.380 align:middle line:90%
>>GRIFFIN: Yeah.

00:39:14.380 --> 00:39:16.250 align:middle line:84%
And they don't want
to own the country

00:39:16.250 --> 00:39:18.010 align:middle line:84%
in terms of real
estate, but they

00:39:18.010 --> 00:39:19.410 align:middle line:90%
want to own it politically.

00:39:19.410 --> 00:39:19.810 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yes.

00:39:19.810 --> 00:39:20.820 align:middle line:84%
>>GRIFFIN: They
want the people--

00:39:20.820 --> 00:39:21.730 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: They want the control.

00:39:21.730 --> 00:39:23.021 align:middle line:90%
>>GRIFFIN: --the control of it.

00:39:23.021 --> 00:39:26.290 align:middle line:84%
And that has been going
on ever since-- well,

00:39:26.290 --> 00:39:28.130 align:middle line:84%
ever since the United
Nations was formed.

00:39:28.130 --> 00:39:28.930 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:39:28.930 --> 00:39:32.360 align:middle line:84%
You look at these countries, the
ones that are getting trashed

00:39:32.360 --> 00:39:35.070 align:middle line:84%
are the ones that
are resisting that.

00:39:35.070 --> 00:39:38.630 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Would you put this
back on the gold standard?

00:39:38.630 --> 00:39:39.870 align:middle line:90%
>>GRIFFIN: Absolutely.

00:39:39.870 --> 00:39:41.406 align:middle line:90%
Or some standard at least.

00:39:41.406 --> 00:39:42.780 align:middle line:84%
I don't care what
standard it is.

00:39:42.780 --> 00:39:45.360 align:middle line:84%
Whatever people want, they
ought to have whatever standard

00:39:45.360 --> 00:39:46.310 align:middle line:90%
they want.

00:39:46.310 --> 00:39:48.310 align:middle line:84%
Most people want some
kind of a standard,

00:39:48.310 --> 00:39:51.140 align:middle line:84%
they don't want some
politician's word.

00:39:51.140 --> 00:39:54.479 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: To date, we have
nothing backing up our money.

00:39:54.479 --> 00:39:55.770 align:middle line:90%
>>GRIFFIN: Except our military.

00:39:55.770 --> 00:39:56.590 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's it.

00:39:56.590 --> 00:39:57.240 align:middle line:90%
>>GRIFFIN: That's it.

00:39:57.240 --> 00:39:58.448 align:middle line:90%
And that's a lot, by the way.

00:39:58.448 --> 00:40:00.040 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It may
be more than gold.

00:40:00.040 --> 00:40:01.998 align:middle line:84%
>>GRIFFIN: In fact, that's
how they look at it.

00:40:01.998 --> 00:40:04.090 align:middle line:84%
As long as we have
the supreme military,

00:40:04.090 --> 00:40:07.560 align:middle line:84%
we can demand anything we want
in any country and if they

00:40:07.560 --> 00:40:10.730 align:middle line:84%
don't comply-- if they
don't accept our dollars,

00:40:10.730 --> 00:40:13.920 align:middle line:84%
for example, in
international trade, well,

00:40:13.920 --> 00:40:16.435 align:middle line:84%
all we have to do is declare
them as a rogue nation--

00:40:16.435 --> 00:40:17.640 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And take them out.

00:40:17.640 --> 00:40:19.515 align:middle line:84%
>>GRIFFIN: --and send
the Marines in and say,

00:40:19.515 --> 00:40:20.920 align:middle line:84%
look at the good
job we're doing.

00:40:20.920 --> 00:40:22.390 align:middle line:90%
We're fighting terrorism.

00:40:22.390 --> 00:40:23.870 align:middle line:90%
And they're gone.

00:40:23.870 --> 00:40:25.830 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Now,
countries like Russia,

00:40:25.830 --> 00:40:28.820 align:middle line:84%
who would love their
rubles to replace

00:40:28.820 --> 00:40:30.065 align:middle line:90%
the dollar, what do they do?

00:40:30.065 --> 00:40:32.690 align:middle line:10%
>>GRIFFIN: Well, they're trying
to do the same thing, actually.

00:40:32.690 --> 00:40:34.060 align:middle line:90%
They want the game.

00:40:34.060 --> 00:40:36.030 align:middle line:84%
They want to play the
game, except they want

00:40:36.030 --> 00:40:37.600 align:middle line:90%
their game instead of our game.

00:40:37.600 --> 00:40:38.990 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You can't blame them.

00:40:38.990 --> 00:40:40.530 align:middle line:90%
>>GRIFFIN: Well, no.

00:40:40.530 --> 00:40:43.380 align:middle line:84%
You can't blame them if
that's your mentality

00:40:43.380 --> 00:40:46.770 align:middle line:84%
to rule and to steal from
your fellow human beings

00:40:46.770 --> 00:40:48.680 align:middle line:84%
and do it politically
and do it legally.

00:40:48.680 --> 00:40:50.850 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, you can't
blame them unless you

00:40:50.850 --> 00:40:52.390 align:middle line:84%
look at it ethically,
which I think

00:40:52.390 --> 00:40:54.180 align:middle line:90%
is the way we should look at.

00:40:54.180 --> 00:40:55.950 align:middle line:84%
It's a terrible crime
to commit against

00:40:55.950 --> 00:40:57.487 align:middle line:90%
your fellow human beings.

00:40:57.487 --> 00:40:58.570 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah, absolutely.

00:40:58.570 --> 00:40:59.420 align:middle line:90%
But they don't care.

00:40:59.420 --> 00:41:00.544 align:middle line:90%
>>GRIFFIN: They don't care.

00:41:00.544 --> 00:41:03.180 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And that's the big
difference with all of this.

00:41:03.180 --> 00:41:06.820 align:middle line:84%
The average person who
collects a paycheck,

00:41:06.820 --> 00:41:10.870 align:middle line:84%
who owns a car, who's trying
to make their mortgage,

00:41:10.870 --> 00:41:13.190 align:middle line:90%
does this affect him at all?

00:41:13.190 --> 00:41:15.020 align:middle line:84%
>>GRIFFIN: It affects
him from the moment

00:41:15.020 --> 00:41:17.370 align:middle line:84%
he awakes to the moment
he goes back to sleep

00:41:17.370 --> 00:41:20.400 align:middle line:90%
because it affects two things.

00:41:20.400 --> 00:41:25.260 align:middle line:84%
It affects the purchasing
power of his hourly wage.

00:41:25.260 --> 00:41:27.720 align:middle line:84%
Inflation is the
word we put to that.

00:41:27.720 --> 00:41:31.700 align:middle line:84%
He works like a dog or
she works like a cat,

00:41:31.700 --> 00:41:34.070 align:middle line:84%
however you want to keep
the genders straight here,

00:41:34.070 --> 00:41:36.760 align:middle line:84%
to make a living and
they put money aside

00:41:36.760 --> 00:41:39.210 align:middle line:84%
for their old age or to
send their kids to school.

00:41:39.210 --> 00:41:41.830 align:middle line:84%
Meanwhile, these hidden
forces are whittling away

00:41:41.830 --> 00:41:46.640 align:middle line:84%
at those dollars or whatever
monetary unit it is,

00:41:46.640 --> 00:41:48.380 align:middle line:84%
and they're stealing
it literally.

00:41:48.380 --> 00:41:51.270 align:middle line:84%
So it's a terrible,
terrible system.

00:41:51.270 --> 00:41:54.369 align:middle line:84%
And how can I say--
I don't know where

00:41:54.369 --> 00:41:55.910 align:middle line:84%
I was going with
that, except that we

00:41:55.910 --> 00:41:59.410 align:middle line:90%
have to break that system.

00:41:59.410 --> 00:42:01.260 align:middle line:84%
It's not something
I would support.

00:42:01.260 --> 00:42:03.190 align:middle line:90%
It's not sustainable.

00:42:03.190 --> 00:42:07.690 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: If we're around
50 years from now, Ed,

00:42:07.690 --> 00:42:08.830 align:middle line:10%
how old will I be?

00:42:08.830 --> 00:42:10.580 align:middle line:90%
I don't think I'll be here.

00:42:10.580 --> 00:42:11.514 align:middle line:90%
You might be.

00:42:11.514 --> 00:42:12.430 align:middle line:90%
>>GRIFFIN: Another 50.

00:42:12.430 --> 00:42:16.080 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Would you be in shock
if the Federal Reserve were

00:42:16.080 --> 00:42:19.700 align:middle line:90%
still around 50 years from now?

00:42:19.700 --> 00:42:22.500 align:middle line:84%
>>GRIFFIN: I wouldn't expect
the Federal Reserve to exist

00:42:22.500 --> 00:42:24.403 align:middle line:90%
as such 50 years from now.

00:42:24.403 --> 00:42:25.653 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It will be different.

00:42:25.653 --> 00:42:26.500 align:middle line:90%
>>GRIFFIN: Yeah.

00:42:26.500 --> 00:42:28.766 align:middle line:84%
Depending on which
scenario we take.

00:42:28.766 --> 00:42:33.020 align:middle line:84%
If we say that everything
continues without change,

00:42:33.020 --> 00:42:34.900 align:middle line:84%
I think the Federal
Reserve will be

00:42:34.900 --> 00:42:38.190 align:middle line:84%
absorbed in some kind of an
international equivalent.

00:42:38.190 --> 00:42:39.080 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yes.

00:42:39.080 --> 00:42:41.080 align:middle line:84%
As we move toward this
one world government.

00:42:41.080 --> 00:42:41.880 align:middle line:90%
>>GRIFFIN: Yeah.

00:42:41.880 --> 00:42:43.690 align:middle line:90%
That's where they want it to go.

00:42:43.690 --> 00:42:45.660 align:middle line:90%
So that's one scenario.

00:42:45.660 --> 00:42:46.527 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Cashless?

00:42:46.527 --> 00:42:47.860 align:middle line:90%
>>GRIFFIN: It would be cashless.

00:42:47.860 --> 00:42:48.860 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, that's part of it.

00:42:48.860 --> 00:42:51.300 align:middle line:84%
So you can't really escape any
record of your transaction.

00:42:51.300 --> 00:42:53.220 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What happens
if the grid goes down,

00:42:53.220 --> 00:42:55.350 align:middle line:84%
the power grid
goes and and we're

00:42:55.350 --> 00:43:00.730 align:middle line:84%
tied into all these electronic
figures and digits and people

00:43:00.730 --> 00:43:04.340 align:middle line:84%
don't have access
to anything anymore?

00:43:04.340 --> 00:43:08.640 align:middle line:84%
If the computer systems go down,
so does your monetary system

00:43:08.640 --> 00:43:10.485 align:middle line:90%
at that point.

00:43:10.485 --> 00:43:11.860 align:middle line:84%
>>GRIFFIN: If the
grid goes down,

00:43:11.860 --> 00:43:13.730 align:middle line:84%
George, this is the
worst case scenario

00:43:13.730 --> 00:43:20.430 align:middle line:84%
I can imagine unless the Earth
collides with another planet.

00:43:20.430 --> 00:43:22.580 align:middle line:84%
But they're in a similar
vein because it's

00:43:22.580 --> 00:43:25.610 align:middle line:84%
the end of everything
we know as life.

00:43:25.610 --> 00:43:29.610 align:middle line:84%
When the grid goes down, we
discover then that everything

00:43:29.610 --> 00:43:34.920 align:middle line:84%
we do and have depends on
power, electricity, water

00:43:34.920 --> 00:43:37.080 align:middle line:90%
coming out of the pipe.

00:43:37.080 --> 00:43:39.500 align:middle line:84%
It depends on
electricity, really.

00:43:39.500 --> 00:43:41.065 align:middle line:84%
That's our primary
source of energy.

00:43:41.065 --> 00:43:44.190 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: It's going to be
an interesting future, Ed.

00:43:44.190 --> 00:43:46.162 align:middle line:10%
>>GRIFFIN: We need to
do everything to prepare

00:43:46.162 --> 00:43:47.370 align:middle line:10%
and prevent that, by the way.

00:43:47.370 --> 00:43:51.940 align:middle line:10%
It's one of my favorite topics
but we won't go there today.

00:43:51.940 --> 00:43:55.120 align:middle line:10%
But it's a serious danger
and it could happen.

00:43:55.120 --> 00:43:58.162 align:middle line:10%
And the powers that be
are ignoring it primarily

00:43:58.162 --> 00:43:59.620 align:middle line:10%
because they don't
want to face it,

00:43:59.620 --> 00:44:01.882 align:middle line:10%
they don't want to be
responsible for it,

00:44:01.882 --> 00:44:03.840 align:middle line:10%
and they want to pretend
like it doesn't exist.

00:44:03.840 --> 00:44:05.215 align:middle line:90%
But it's very real in my view.

00:44:05.215 --> 00:44:07.090 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Ed, thanks for
being on the program.

00:44:07.090 --> 00:44:07.890 align:middle line:90%
Appreciate it.

00:44:07.890 --> 00:44:09.540 align:middle line:84%
>>GRIFFIN: Thank
you for inviting me.

00:44:09.540 --> 00:44:11.720 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: The Federal
Reserve, we all

00:44:11.720 --> 00:44:13.655 align:middle line:84%
have thought-- even
I did-- that it

00:44:13.655 --> 00:44:15.830 align:middle line:90%
was part of the US government.

00:44:15.830 --> 00:44:16.790 align:middle line:90%
It is not.

00:44:16.790 --> 00:44:21.750 align:middle line:84%
Is a private cartel owned
by major banks dictating

00:44:21.750 --> 00:44:27.070 align:middle line:84%
policy to our government,
dictating how we live.

00:44:27.070 --> 00:44:28.290 align:middle line:10%
We've got to fight back.

00:44:28.290 --> 00:44:29.500 align:middle line:10%
I'm George Noory.

00:44:29.500 --> 00:44:31.330 align:middle line:90%
This is "Beyond Belief."

00:44:31.330 --> 00:44:34.080 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:44:34.080 --> 00:44:38.351 align:middle line:90%